s=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5755840\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5755840\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qsj1704711355836.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qsj1704711355836.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qsj1704711355836.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qvm1665702757744\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Image Handling\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface can display and print pictures that are stored as image files on disk, as glyphs, or BLOBs in a database. The type of picture can affect performance.\n </p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Referencing Pictures</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__1\">\n Notation\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__3\">\n Performance Impact\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">@</code>\n</p>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__2\">\n Load the image from the disk file <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__3\">\n Loading an image from disk is far more expensive in terms of I/O than loading the equivalent glyph.\n <p class=\"p\">This is not an important consideration if you do not need to do this very often, or you do it only temporarily in the Uniface IDE.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">#</code>\n</p>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldName</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__2\">\n Load the image from the BLOB field <var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldName</var>.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__3\">\n Depending on your DBMS, loading a BLOB from the database is probably faster than loading a disk file.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&amp;</code>\n</p>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">URL</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__2\">\n In server pages only, display the image specified by the URL.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__3\">\n In web applications, this is the fastest way to load images. Uniface is not actually involved in displaying the image, and depending on the environment, images may be loaded from cache.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">^</code>\n</p>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Glyph</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__2\">\n Load the glyph named <var class=\"keyword varname\">Glyph</var>.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qvm1665702757744__table_d1238e1_d1239e1_d1240e1__entry__3\">\n Glyphs are Uniface-proprietary compiled images that may be used in desktop applications. The location of glyphs depends on the configuration, but may be in a UAR file or the Repository.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__p_d11819e1_d11820e1_d11821e1\">Fields of any data type can be picture fields:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__li_d5420e1_d5421e1_d5422e1\">Fields with data type Image—images, glyphs, or BLOBs are loaded automatically\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__li_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1\">Fields with data type String—images and glyphs (but not BLOBs) are loaded automatically if the data uses the picture notation. If the string picture field does not conform to this syntax, a ValRep list must be defined.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__li_d5426e1_d5427e1_d5428e1\">Fields with other data types—require a ValRep list to load an image or glyph because Uniface needs to know how the data in the field should be interpreted.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qvm1665702757744__p_d11822e1_d11823e1_d11824e1\">If no path is specified for an image file (<code class=\"ph codeph\">@</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>), Uniface looks for the image in the current directory or in the directory specified by the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zrt1665702757821.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrt1665702757821.html\" title=\"Specifies the name of the directory where image files are stored. You can specify more than one directory by using a comma-separated list.\">Images</a> assignment setting. If you use an explicit path to specify an image, this setting is ignored.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbf1705582294349.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Glyphs</a><p>Glyphs are images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5755840\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5755840\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Image Handling Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Image Handling Uniface can display and print pictures that are stored as image files on disk, as glyphs, or BLOBs in a database. The type of picture can affect performance. Table 1. Referencing Pictures Notation Meaning Performance Impact @ FileName Load the image from the disk file FileName . Loading an image from disk is far more expensive in terms of I/O than loading the equivalent glyph. This is not an important consideration if you do not need to do this very often, or you do it only temporarily in the Uniface IDE. # FieldName Load the image from the BLOB field FieldName . Depending on your DBMS, loading a BLOB from the database is probably faster than loading a disk file. & URL In server pages only, display the image specified by the URL. In web applications, this is the fastest way to load images. Uniface is not actually involved in displaying the image, and depending on the environment, images may be loaded from cache. ^ Glyph Load the glyph named Glyph . Glyphs are Uniface-proprietary compiled images that may be used in desktop applications. The location of glyphs depends on the configuration, but may be in a UAR file or the Repository. Fields of any data type can be picture fields: Fields with data type Image—images, glyphs, or BLOBs are loaded automatically Fields with data type String—images and glyphs (but not BLOBs) are loaded automatically if the data uses the picture notation. If the string picture field does not conform to this syntax, a ValRep list must be defined. Fields with other data types—require a ValRep list to load an image or glyph because Uniface needs to know how the data in the field should be interpreted. If no path is specified for an image file ( @ FileName ), Uniface looks for the image in the current directory or in the directory specified by the Images assignment setting. If you use an explicit path to specify an image, this setting is ignored. Related Links Glyphs Glyphs are images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}